7.1. In Situ DSC Analysis of Solid-Solid Phase Transformations in Precipitation Hardening Alloys
In the past 10 to 15 years, the dynamic range of in situ DSC on age-hardening alloys has been
substantially extended, particularly in terms of continuous cooling experiments. A range of
to 3 K/s can now be applied in a reliable analysis method using
direct, in situ DSC experiments. Based on a typical temperature interval for the cooling of light
metal alloys from solution treatment, this is equivalent to cooling durations ranging from several
weeks up to a few minutes.
